title: A Book of Nonsense
creator: Edward Lear
description: LibriVox recording of A Book of Nonsense by Edward Lear. Read by Phil Chenevert. In 1846 Lear published A Book of Nonsense, a volume of limericks that went through three editions and helped popularize the form. This book contains 112 of these funny, imaginative verses that have been well loved by many generations of children (and adults). ( Summary by Phil Chenevert ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: audiobook; librivox; limerick; rimes; verses; children; humour; humor; nonsense
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
